      • setRules

        public EnumFormatValidator.Builder setRules(Rules rules)
        Parameters:
        rules - The validation rules: it should be an instance of HashMap. It should contains at least one keys: 1) "correct", 2) suggestions (which is optional), whose values need to be an instance of java.util.List. The value of the key "correct" consist of a list of accepted columns (that is if the user enter an entry that belongs to a entries in one of the columns, we accept the user's entry), otherwise if the user has entered an entries in the list of "suggestions" value's column, then the error message will provide hint that allows user to enter the value in the corrected column
        Returns:
        return an instance of FormatValidatorBuilder with rules being initialized
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the input is null or the rules does not contain at least one 'correct' column, which the Validator will accept if the entry comes from that column

      • loadDataGzip

        public EnumFormatValidator.Builder loadDataGzip()
        Read the gzip file from the given file path, then convert it into an instance of Table object, which can be saved to a specified directory later through calling the saveTo method. This methods assumes that the row of the columns are split by a new line, and the first row should specify the column names. Also make sure that each entry does not contain any character that you use to split each entry in the row, or else the behavior may be undefined
        Returns:
        the FormatValidatorBuilder with the table initialized
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - when any error occurs while reading the gzip file

      • retrieveIndices

        private java.lang.String retrieveIndices(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> secondaryIndices)
        This method determines the primary index given the correct and suggested columns from the Rules object. It returns the primary index and fill the empty secondaryIndex ArrayList with the correct secondary index. The primary index will be the first column name in the correct field of the Rules object.
        Parameters:
        secondaryIndices - the ArrayList of String that will be filled
        Returns:
        the primary index given the Rules object

      • loadData

        public EnumFormatValidator.Builder loadData()
        Does everything that the loadDataGzip does, except it works for text file instead. Note it is not recommended to use this method since it is slower.
        Returns:
        the FormatValidatorBuilder with the table initialized
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - throw exception when reading file fails

      • populateTable

        private void populateTable(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> secondaryIndices,
                           java.lang.String primaryIndex,
                           java.io.BufferedReader reader)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        Fill the table given a list of secondary indices and primary indices. This method does not checker its argument, therefore it is the caller's responsibility to ensure the argument is valid. Because of that, this is a private method
        Parameters:
        secondaryIndices - the secondary indices
        primaryIndex - the primary index
        reader - a BufferedReader that reads the gzip file line by line
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any error occurs while reading the gzip file
